<!-- signup loader -->
<% if request.referer == signup_url %>
  <div class="signup_loader">
    <%= image_tag "page-loader.gif" %>
    <h3> nowpage.com/<%= @user.url %> <br> is being born. </h3>
  </div> 
<% end %>

<!-- header -->
<div class="simple_header">
  <% if request.referer == signup_url %>
    --> <%= link_to "EDIT LAYOUT", user_profile_edit_path, class: "edit_profile_link" %>
  <% else %>
    <!-- discriminate btw users that are not logged in and those that are -->
    <% unless user_logged_in? %>
      <%= link_to "What is a nowpage?", "", id: "explain_now_link" %> |
      <%= link_to "Login & Edit", login_path %>
    <% else %>
      <%= link_to "Edit Nowpage", user_profile_edit_path, class: "btn btn-md btn-success" %> |
      <%= link_to "Logout", logout_path %>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
</div>

<!-- explain what nowpage is -->
<div class="explain_now" id="whatev">
  A Nowpage is a public declaration of priorities. It is where you state to yourself and to others what you are focusing on now. The nowpage movement has been started by Derek Sivers. Many people have begun to add nowpages to their own websites. Many find it an uplifting and valuable thing to do. They say it helps them focus.
</div>

<!-- after signup directions -->
<% if request.referer == signup_url %>
  <div class="after_signup_directions">
    <i class="fa fa-times fa-lg" id="close" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    <strong> You are now online. </strong> <br>
    You can edit your layout anytime you log in or here: <br>
    <%= link_to "Edit layout.", "#" %> <br> <br> 
  </div>
<% end %>


<!-- central content -->
<div class="simple_container">
  
  <!-- title -->
  <% if @title.nil? || @title.empty? %>
    <h1> What Iâ€™m doing now </h1>
  <% else %>
    <h1> <%= @title %> </h1>
  <% end %>

  <!-- subtitle --> 
  <% if @subtitle.nil? || @subtitle.empty? %>
    <h3> Johannes R. Seikowsky (Layout) </h3>
  <% else %>
    <h3> <%= @subtitle %> </h3>
  <% end %>

  <!-- content --> 
  <% if @content.nil? || @content.empty? %>
    <p>
      These are the most important things I currently focus on:
      Places - My girlfriend and I are trying an experiment of living in different, interesting places for a couple of months each. Enough to properly internalize each place. Right now we are in Tel Aviv for 3 months and it's going well. 2) Programming- I hack. This site is my latest project. I've done a few others and have a long pipeline of ideas ahead of me. I'm also learning more about penetration testing, as part of which I'm expanding from Ruby to Python. I write. I try not to, but somehow always end up producing something sometimes. By now there are almost 20 blog posts by me. You can find them on medium.<br> <%= link_to "Edit this layout.", "#" %>
    </p>
  <% else %>
    <p> <%= @content %> </p>
  <% end %>

  <!-- profile image -->
  <br> 
  <%= image_tag "johannes.jpg", class: "img-responsive img-circle", style: "width:68%; margin: 15px 16% 15px 16%;" %>
  <br>

  <!-- contact section -->  
  <% if @contact_text.nil? || @contact_text.empty? %>
    <p> 
      I'm interested in programming, writing, research and teaching. Please feel free to get in touch about collaborating on any project concerned with these interests.
    </p>
  <% else %>
    <p> <%= @contact_text %> </p>
  <% end %>

  <form>
    <textarea></textarea>
    <input type="submit" value="Send" >
  </form>
</div>


<!-- js -->
<script type="text/javascript">
  // fadeOut loader graphic
  $(window).load(function() {
    $(".signup_loader").delay(5500).fadeOut("slow");
  })
  // close button for after-signup-directions div
  $('#close').click(function(){
    $('.after_signup_directions').css("display", "none");
  });
  // toggling explain_now visibility
  $("#explain_now_link").hover(function(){
    $('.explain_now').css("display", "inline");
    }, function(){
    $('.explain_now').css("display", "none");
  });
</script>


